<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've been getting pretty frustrated lately with groups that continually ingnore the value of my mezz. Yes, I know how to properly mezz and I'm properly specced in mind (about 75%). I'd say my mez sticks about 90% of the time on reds and 65% on purples. Oranges and yellows don't stand a chance  What I find is tanks, and even clerics (sigh) repeatedly breaking my mezzes. Now I'm in Keltoi, and there's not a whole lot of room to work with so many times the mezzed mob(s) are within melee distance from my group. We always designate a main assist and talk about how we'll stay on the same target and let me mezz but all too often that is ignored in combat. Sure I can just stand back and debuff but how fun it that? My true group strength is in keeping the mobs at bay. <P>I have been in several groups that raved about my mezz but lately I've hit a brick wall. I politely excused myself from 2 groups yesterday because I was frustrated. Does anyone have any advice on how to handle these situations? At 22nd, is there a new place with social mobs I can go to to escape the close quarters of Keltoi? I'm curious to see what other sorcerers do in these situations. Maybe I'm just making too much of it and should bite my tongue. I just hate to see us needlessly fighting 3 or 4 mobs. <P>Thanks, <BR>Meryelle Incantare <BR>21 seasons/Guinivere
</FONT>
