<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, a group that is trained well to handle 2s and 3s will survive when you get an unexpected six pack.<P>However, I find groups don't care if they're breaking your mez.  Why?  They don't see any consequences.  Who cares if the group fights 2 or 3 at a time...  There are two clerics, no one dies, there isn't even much time for medding.<P>Unless it can be related to them getting experience, it doesn't get through.  You can try relating it to...<P>-deaths (if any)<BR>-downtime (clerics needing to med)<BR>-exp (more exp with group bonus)<P>I had a group just like this in Keltoi the other night...  They were happy to fight 2 or 3 all at once, since it wasn't impacting the battles they didn't care.   It all changed when we wanted to attack a room of 4.  We'd lost a few members, and were only at 5 ourselves so some were skeptical.<P>I said I'll ae mez, we made sure what mob we were fighting first and who would pick the next target.  Of course it went smoothly.  After that they paid more attention to mez.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>It has to be seen to be believed I guess.  If they won't go with it, I just nuke (haven't completely ignored my body) and maybe use a pet if one is available.
</FONT>
