Honestly, pre lvl 37, If I got in a group I just felt so damn lucky that I just didnt even say more than a few words about the mezzez.  Like "who is MA, please assist" or "I can AE mez very well if you would like to use it, if not I will debuff/nuke", ect... after my initial appeal if there was a rouge element in the group that couldnt figure out how to use mez, then I would just act like a nuker and let clerics stun or whatever, unless other group members spoke up and said something like "DAMN use assist people and let the sorcerer mez for gosh sakes".  By the time I hit lvl 40 groups knew mez value well enough and I was needed in lyoness, but until then, I was just happy to get a group, as any group killing orange/red is better than any solo xp. <P>Burzumishi<BR>lvl 44.5 sorcerer <BR>bevedere
